<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10109104>
    dc:description "FIGURE 44. Australogryllacris guttata sp. nov., holotype male: A, habitus dorsal view; B, face, C, apical area of hind femur with enlarged spines; D–I abdominal apex in lateral view (D), with cercus flipped aside (E), in apical view showing projections of tenth abdominal tergite (F, G), in ventral (H) and oblique ventral view (I) showing three-lobate subgenital plate and projections of tenth abdominal tergite from behind." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10109104/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

